Adelaide Club Australia.formatted_address: 165 North Terrace, Adelaide, South Australia 5000, Australia
Adelaide Club Australia.name: Adelaide Club Australia
Adelaide Club Australia.description: Founded in 1863, the Adelaide Club is an exclusive gentlemen’s club and one of Australia’s oldest private clubs​:contentReference[oaicite:13]{index=13}. Its heritage clubhouse on North Terrace offers dining rooms, a billiards room, meeting spaces, accommodation suites, and a distinguished environment for socializing and networking among Adelaide’s business and community leaders.

Lyceum Club Adelaide.formatted_address: Level 1, 20-24 Leigh Street, Adelaide, South Australia 5000, Australia
Lyceum Club Adelaide.name: Lyceum Club Adelaide
Lyceum Club Adelaide.description: A private women’s club in Adelaide for those interested in arts, literature, science and public affairs. Founded in 1922 (part of the International Association of Lyceum Clubs), it provides a venue for lectures, discussion groups, and cultural activities in an apolitical, non-sectarian environment, fostering friendship and intellectual exchange among its members​:contentReference[oaicite:14]{index=14}.

Naval, Military & Air Force Club of Sout.formatted_address: 111 Hutt Street, Adelaide, South Australia 5000, Australia
Naval, Military & Air Force Club of Sout.name: Naval, Military & Air Force Club of South Australia Inc.
Naval, Military & Air Force Club of Sout.description: A prestigious private military-origin club tracing its roots to 1879​:contentReference[oaicite:15]{index=15}. Originally an officers’ club, it now welcomes members of all backgrounds. The clubhouse offers elegant dining, a bar, library and reading rooms, and boutique accommodation. The club’s atmosphere honors tradition and service heritage while providing a social and networking hub for its members​:contentReference[oaicite:16]{index=16}​:contentReference[oaicite:17]{index=17}.

Public Schools Club.formatted_address: 207 East Terrace, Adelaide, South Australia 5000, Australia
Public Schools Club.name: Public Schools Club
Public Schools Club.description: Established in 1959 by alumni of Adelaide’s elite schools​:contentReference[oaicite:18]{index=18}, this private club (housed in historic Sandford House) offers a collegial atmosphere for graduates. It features a restaurant (open to public as “Club Bragg’s”), function rooms, a bar and accommodation. The club continues to uphold traditions of academic excellence and camaraderie, now welcoming male and female graduates from any school​:contentReference[oaicite:19]{index=19}​:contentReference[oaicite:20]{index=20}.

Queen Adelaide Club.formatted_address: North Terrace, Adelaide, South Australia 5000, Australia
Queen Adelaide Club.name: Queen Adelaide Club
Queen Adelaide Club.description: Founded in 1909, the Queen Adelaide Club is an exclusive women’s club offering a refined environment for social interaction, cultural activities, and networking. Located on North Terrace, it provides dining and lounge facilities and maintains a tradition of philanthropy and community service involvement among its members. Membership is by invitation, continuing a legacy as Adelaide’s premier ladies’ club.
